{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772613500,"nonce":"O0nXPpHCq0KKaHLyIDdZsXT41R0=","title":"feat: department member management view","message":"## Problem\n\nThere is no way to manage department members from the department page. Currently, to add a user to a department you have to find the user, edit them, and change their role dropdown for that specific department. This is unintuitive, especially when adding someone to multiple departments.\n\n## Solution\n\n### 1. New department members management view\n\nAdd a new route `/werkstaetten/:id/members/edit` with a filter list UI (same pattern as items and borrowers filter lists). From this view:\n\n- See all current members and their roles\n- Add existing users to the department (with role assignment)\n- Remove users from the department\n- Change roles of existing members\n\nThis view is accessible from the department detail page (`/werkstaetten/:id`) alongside the existing \"bearbeiten\" link for department metadata.\n\n### 2. Link from user views to department member management\n\n- **User edit view** (`/users/:id/edit`): Show which departments the user belongs to. Each department links to `/werkstaetten/:id/members/edit`.\n- **Staff list view** (`/verwaltung/verleihende`): The department groupings link to `/werkstaetten/:id/members/edit`.\n\n### UI Pattern\n\nThe member management view should use the same filter list pattern already used for items and borrowers — searchable, filterable list with inline actions.","files":null}]}